cs.MA, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the interaction between two species in a game-theoretic framework.
- cs.GT (Game Theory) is also likely as the paper explicitly mentions the use of a game to model the exchange of environmental information.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper uses information-theoretic interpretations to relate the growth rate of the species to their knowledge of the environment.
- cs.SI (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper models the dynamics of the two species in the world.
- cs.SY (Control Systems) is also relevant as the paper deals with the control of the growth of the two species in a scenario with limited resources.
